Craig,

First, if any name under domain .IL will be valid then many resolvers
will have alot of garbage in their caches if .IL becomes a popular
domain.

Second, is it not frustrating to send mail to someone and have it
come back a few days later saying "wrong host"? The frustration
increases if you have to try to figure out what the right host name
is and you can not use the domain system to verify the correct
spelling? Do you really want to cause this kind of frustration among
the growing number of non-hacker users?

The aggravation of updating data is significant but less significant
as aggravating a large segment of people locally and elsewhere that
make typos and minor mistakes.

As someone corrected me on my model of the telephone system, the
second set of 3 digits on a long distance call are verified by the
local system.  Bell did this to reduce traffic over the long distance
trunks and to improve response to dialers. We should learn from this
decision.

-Rudy

